## Phase 0: System Discovery (Classify Before You Build)

Mixed systems need **multiple lenses**. A hospital app is software + clinical workflow + regulatory + human factors.

### 0A — System class taxonomy (pick all that apply)

#### Information & computation
| Class | Primary questions | Typical failures |
|---|---|---|
| Request/response service | Who calls? SLA? Idempotency? | Timeouts, partial writes, thundering herd |
| Event/stream processor | Ordering? Delivery semantics? | Duplicates, lag, poison messages |
| Batch / scheduled job | Window? Backfill? Idempotent runs? | Double runs, late data, resource spikes |
| Stateful application | Source of truth? Cache coherency? | Stale reads, lost updates, split brain |
| Data store / schema / catalog | Access patterns? Migration? Lineage? | Lock contention, drift, silent corruption |
| Client surface (any UI/device) | Offline? Permissions? Latency perception? | Race conditions, token leakage, a11y gaps |
| Library / SDK / standard | Stability contract? Versioning? | Breaking consumers, ambiguous spec |
| Agent / ML / decision support | Ground truth? Nondeterminism? Oversight? | Hallucination, bias, runaway cost, automation bias |
| Platform / infra / tooling | Blast radius? Rollback? Multi-tenant isolation? | Cascading failure, config drift |

#### Physical & operational
| Class | Primary questions | Typical failures |
|---|---|---|
| Manufacturing / assembly | Yield? Bottleneck? WIP limits? | Defect cascades, line stoppage, unsafe bypass |
| Supply chain / logistics | Lead time variance? Single source? | Stockouts, bullwhip effect, spoilage |
| Inventory / warehousing | FIFO/FEFO? Cycle count? Shrink? | Phantom inventory, mis-pick, expiry waste |
| Fleet / routing / field ops | Utilization? SLA geography? | Missed windows, deadhead miles, technician overload |
| Facilities / energy / utilities | Capacity? Redundancy? Maintenance cycles? | Brownouts, run-to-failure, safety interlock bypass |
| Construction / deployment (physical) | Critical path? Inspection gates? | Rework, code violations, weather delays |

#### Human & organizational
| Class | Primary questions | Typical failures |
|---|---|---|
| Workflow / SOP | Handoffs? Escalation? Exceptions? | Shadow processes, rubber-stamping, bottlenecks |
| Org / team topology | Ownership? Decision rights? Bus factor? | Diffusion of responsibility, silos, review theater |
| Incentive / performance system | What's measured? What's gamed? | Perverse incentives, metric fixation, moral hazard |
| Training / onboarding | Competency proof? Refresh cadence? | Procedure drift, unqualified operators |
| Customer support / success | Tiering? Knowledge base? | Repeat tickets, empathy burnout, wrong deflection |
| Sales / GTM motion | Cycle length? Channel conflict? | Discount spirals, bad-fit customers, churn bombs |

#### Economic & market
| Class | Primary questions | Typical failures |
|---|---|---|
| Pricing / packaging | Willingness to pay? Margin floor? | Race to bottom, surprise bills, adverse selection |
| Marketplace / two-sided | Liquidity? Trust? Disintermediation? | Chicken-and-egg, fraud, platform leakage |
| Financial / ledger | Conservation laws? Reconciliation? | Double entry errors, settlement gaps, fraud |
| Risk / insurance / reserves | Tail risks? Correlation? | Under-reserved, correlated shocks |

#### Knowledge, policy, creative
| Class | Primary questions | Typical failures |
|---|---|---|
| Policy / governance | Enforcement? Exceptions? Appeals? | Unenforceable rules, regulatory arbitrage |
| Compliance program | Control mapping? Evidence? | Checkbox compliance, audit panic, control gaps |
| Research / experiment | Hypothesis? Power? Pre-registration? | p-hacking, irreproducibility, confounders |
| Content / media pipeline | Rights? Moderation? Freshness? | Stale content, brand risk, copyright strikes |
| Design system / brand | Tokens? Accessibility? Consistency? | Fragmentation, inaccessible patterns |

#### Hybrid (most real systems)
Cyber-physical (IoT, robotics, AV), socio-technical (EHR + clinicians), fintech (money + software + regulation), edtech (pedagogy + platform + assessment).

**When hybrid:** draw separate sub-diagrams per class, then map **interfaces** where failures propagate.

### 0B — Complexity domain (Cynefin-style routing)

| Domain | Characteristics | Approach |
|---|---|---|
| **Clear** | Known best practice, repeatable | Standard operating procedure; monitor for drift |
| **Complicated** | Expert analysis needed; cause-effect discoverable | Analyze → design → implement; peer review |
| **Complex** | Emergent; cause-effect only clear in hindsight | Probe → sense → respond; safe-to-fail experiments |
| **Chaotic** | Crisis; act first | Stabilize → triage → then analyze |
| **Confused** | Don't know which domain you're in | **Stop.** Gather data. Do not build big bets blindly |

If the user asks for a big build in **Complex** or **Confused** territory, propose **small probes** with explicit learning goals before commitment.

### 0C — Boundary map (always produce for non-trivial work)

```
[Purpose: who benefits, success metric]

[Actors outside boundary] ──→ [Entry points / triggers]
                           ──→ [Control plane: rules, orchestration, policy]
                           ──→ [Operating plane: transforms, work, flows]
                           ──→ [State: stocks, records, inventory, reputation]
                           ──→ [Side effects: money, messages, emissions, legal exposure]
                           ←── [Feedback: metrics, audits, complaints, sensors, P&L]
[Actors outside boundary] ←──
```

### 0D — Stakeholder & incentive map

| Stakeholder | Goal | Fear | Incentive created by your change | Misalignment risk |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| End user | | | | |
| Operator / staff | | | | |
| Buyer (if ≠ user) | | | | |
| Regulator | | | | |
| Competitor | | | | |
| Environment / public | | | | |

**Rule:** If you cannot articulate who loses when you win, you have not finished Phase 0.

### Cross-domain discovery examples

**Software — webhook retries:** event processor + integration; actors = SaaS, API, worker, DB; state = delivery log + idempotency keys.

**Operations — warehouse pick path redesign:** physical flow + human factors; invariant = order accuracy ≥ target; failure = congestion at packing station.

**Policy — remote work approval:** governance + HR workflow; failure = managers bypass with shadow "always approve" culture.

**Healthcare — triage protocol change:** clinical + legal + human; invariant = critical patients never downgraded below evidence-based threshold.

**Manufacturing — add supplier:** supply chain + quality; failure = untested sub-tier component voids certification.

**Education — new grading rubric:** incentive system + knowledge; second-order = students optimize for rubric not learning.

**Finance — dynamic pricing:** market + fairness perception; failure = PR crisis reads as price gouging.

**Research — A/B test new ranking:** experiment + ethics; invariant = no harm to vulnerable cohorts; guardrail metrics required.

