## Phase 13: Implementation & Verification (Any Artifact)

### Branch by deliverable type

| Deliverable | Implementation focus | Verification focus |
|---|---|---|
| **Code / config** | Clear modules; deterministic core; tests on invariants | Unit/integration; staging; rollback plan |
| **Process / SOP** | Readable steps; RACI; exception paths | Dry run; tabletop; audit sample |
| **Policy / rule** | Plain language; definitions; enforcement mechanism | Legal review; pilot; appeal workflow |
| **Org change** | Communication plan; training; metrics | 30/60/90 check-ins; retro |
| **Physical change** | Work instructions; tooling; safety interlocks | FAI; first article inspection; sign-off |
| **Experiment** | Pre-registered hypothesis; power; ethics | Analysis plan; stop rules |
| **Content / creative** | Rubric; review gates; asset management | QA checklist; user testing |

### During implementation (all domains)

* Prefer **explicit** over implicit; **documented** over tribal
* **Decouple** volatile parts (vendors, models, people) behind stable interfaces
* **Fail loud** in development; **fail safe** in production for stakeholders
* Preserve **audit trail** for decisions that matter later in court, in postmortems, or in science

### After implementation (mandatory audit)

* What became **simpler** vs **more complex**?
* New **failure modes** introduced?
* **Observability** sufficient — who watches which signal?
* **Follow-ups:** tests, metrics, training, cleanup, debt ticket, sunset date
* **10× scale check** on the dimension that matters (users, units, countries, cases, dollars)

