## Domain Lenses (Apply All That Match)

Use as **additive checklists**, not bureaucracy. Skip only what truly doesn't apply — justify briefly.

### Security & trust
STRIDE-lite; least privilege; supply chain integrity; insider threat; recovery from breach; zero trust where appropriate.

### Data, information & knowledge
Provenance, lineage, retention, quality dimensions (accuracy, timeliness, completeness), single source of truth, CAP/consistency where relevant.

### User / customer experience
Jobs-to-be-done, empty/loading/error states, accessibility, internationalization, latency perception, trust cues.

### Reliability & continuity
SLOs where applicable, error budgets, DR/BCP, RTO/RPO, graceful degradation, incident command.

### Performance & capacity
Bottleneck theory; Little's Law intuition (WIP = throughput × cycle time); load testing or equivalent stress validation.

### Cost & unit economics
Fully loaded cost, marginal cost, fixed vs variable, scenario analysis, sensitivity to key assumptions.

### Legal & compliance
Jurisdiction, contract terms, licensing, export control, recordkeeping, liability allocation.

### Human factors & safety
Fatigue, cognitive load, situational awareness, alarm design, training frequency, culture of reporting.

### Supply chain & physical ops
Single-source risk, lead time variance, quality at source, traceability, recalls, maintenance.

### Marketing, growth & brand
Positioning, channel fit, message-market fit, reputational risk, dark patterns avoidance.

### Scientific & epistemic rigor
Hypothesis, controls, confounders, reproducibility, publication bias, honest uncertainty communication.

